&gt; I recently wrote an MX mailer according (I thought) to RFC 974.  As I read
&gt; it, one was supposed to eliminate MX records pointing to systems which
&gt; don't sport SMTP WKS records.  I have found there are a large number of
&gt; systems which have MX entries pointing to systems without WKS records.

Bob:

    You do conform to RFC 974.  Unfortunately, demanding people keep
accurate WKS records proved to be a flop.  So you shouldn't bother to 
check for WKS (indeed, the soon-to-be-release Host Requirements will
declare the WKS requirement dead).

Thanks,

Craig

